               <p>ROBERT LOCKTON. I live in <placeName id="t18271025-147-crimeloc852">Wellington-place, St. George's in the East</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18271025-147-crimeloc852" type="placeName" value="Wellington-place, St. George's in the East"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18271025-147-crimeloc852" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18271025-147-off850 t18271025-147-crimeloc852"></join>. The prisoner lodged two or three nights with me; he went out in the morning, and as the sheets were missing, I went and told him he was wanted; he returned till within two doors of the house. and then ran away; I pursued for half a mile, calling Stop thief! and he was taken.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18271025-147-person768">
                  ROBERT 
                  MARSTON
               <interp inst="t18271025-147-person768" type="surname" value="MARSTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18271025-147-person768" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18271025-147-person768" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I heard an alarm - Lockton was pursuing the prisoner - I followed, and saw a man take the sheet from him, and tell him to be off - I took the prisoner, and took the sheet from the other man - he said he was in distress, and had nothing to eat.</p>
